  "prompt": "What do we call Buffalo meat? Is it bacon?",
  "response": "Buffalo meat is not called bacon. The meat from buffalo is typically referred to as \"bison\" or \"bison meat.\" Bison is a type of buffalo native to North America. Bacon specifically refers to cured meat that comes from pigs. While there can be bison bacon (which is cured and prepared like traditional bacon), it is not the same as the meat itself.",
